tweet: If you are asked to evacuate due to #HurricaneDorian, you should do so without delay. For more resources, visit  https://lawson.house.gov/issues/hurricane-preparedness … #HurricanePrep

It's not too early to start getting for the storm. Before #HurricaneDorian makes landfall, determine routes from your home, evacuation zones, shelter locations and places to meet should you be separated from your loved ones.  https://lawson.house.gov/issues/hurricane-preparedness …

#MadisonCounty: Sign up for Code Red Weather Warnings. CodeRED Weather Warning is designed to rapidly alert residents in the path of severe weather  https://madisoncountyfl.com/emergency-management/ …
#LeonCounty: You can download the Citizens Connect App for emergency information and for ways to stay engaged during, and after, and before a severe weather event. #HurricaneDorian2019

#JeffersonCounty: There are two ways to sign up to receive alerts from the Jefferson County Sheriff’s Office: Text 32344 to 888777, or visit  https://www.nixle.com  and sign up with either your email or your phone number.

#HamiltonCounty: Emergency Notices will be available on the Hamilton County Sheriff’s Office FB Page  https://tinyurl.com/y4rmc5la   and Information Line at 386-792-2911. You can also register for Code Red https://tinyurl.com/y6nsznel

#GadsdenCounty: Get alerts about emergencies and other events including severe weather, unexpected road closures, missing persons and evacuations of buildings or neighborhoods  https://tinyurl.com/y23lhduf
#DuvalCounty: AlertJAX is an Emergency Alert & Notification System with info on major incidents, disasters, public health concerns, severe weather, and more  https://tinyurl.com/AlertJAX
#ColumbiaCounty: Register your address and contact information into the ALERT Columbia County FLA portal for alerts on emergencies and severe weather  https://www.columbiacountyfla.com/alerts.html
#BakerCounty: Alert Baker is the Emergency Alert system used in the event of a major weather event or security risk in Baker County  http://www.bakerso.com/alert_baker/
Be Prepared: Stay up to date on severe weather conditions with notifications from your community’s warning system. #HurricaneDorian2019

#MadisonCounty: Sandbags available in preparation for #HurricaneDorian at Madison County EOC, located at 1083 SW Harvey Greene Drive, Madison, Florida. There is a limit of 10 bags per person. Contact Madison County Emergency Management if you have any questions at (850) 973-3698.

#JeffersonCounty: Sandbags will be available on Saturday 9 a.m.-12 p.m. and Sunday 1 p.m.-3 p.m. limit 10 bags per household. Locations - old fire department next to County Road Department, Lloyd between post office and volunteer fire department, Wacissa at the old post office.
#HamiltonCounty: Offering sand bags at the Annex. For more information contact Hamilton Emergency Services. More #HurricaneDorian info at:  https://lawson.house.gov/issues/hurricane-preparedness …

#GadsdenCounty: A sandbag location will open Thursday from 10 a.m. until 5 p.m. at the Post Plant Pit, 1090 Post Plant Road, Quincy, FL. Households limited to 15 sandbags, please bring shovels. For elderly and special needs citizens, Gadsden Public Works will be on hand to help.

#DuvalCounty: Work crews began clearing Jacksonville drainage systems. County is not providing sandbags. Residents are instructed to check local Home Depots or local home appliance stores for sand bag information. #HurricaneDorian2019 #JaxReady

#ColumbiaCounty - Announcement regarding possible sandbag locations expected later this afternoon. Please continue to monitor the Columbia County Emergency Management Facebook page for more information. #HurricaneDorian #floridahurricane

#BakerCounty: Sandbags will be made available from 9:00 a.m. to 5:00 p.m. this Friday, Saturday, and Sunday at the City Yard location on 764 Hartline Drive. Limit of 10 bags per household – be prepared to show valid proof of residency. #HurricaneDorian

#Tallahassee: Sandbags are available at James Messer Park South (2830 Jackson Bluff Rd), and the old Northwood Mall (1940 N. Monroe St). Residents are asked to bring their own shovels. There is a 25-bag limit per household. #HurricaneDorian #HurricanePrep  https://lawson.house.gov/issues/hurricane-preparedness …

A state of emergency has been declared for parts of #Florida as #HurricaneDorian moves closer. Residents should ensure they have a plan in place & prepare for strong winds and heavy rain. Sandbags are available in #TLH and #GadsdenCounty. Stay updated:  https://lawson.house.gov/issues/hurricane-preparedness …

Preparation is key to ensuring you stay safe during the storm. As we prepare for the effects of #HurricaneDorian, make sure to stock up on non-perishable food, bottled water, flashlights, batteries, medication, & any other necessities to last up to 7 days  https://www.ready.gov/build-a-kit

Forecasts show #TropicalStormDorian's winds & rain could begin to affect #Florida by the weekend, and upgrade to a #hurricane. While the intensity of #Dorian remains uncertain, prepare for impacts, including strong winds, heavy rain, and possible flooding. https://www.npr.org/2019/08/28/754984058/dorian-will-hit-florida-as-category-2-hurricane-new-forecast-says …
